Acts 7-4 <f>ⓕ</f> Then he went out from the land of the Chaldeans and lived in Haran. And <f>ⓖ</f>after his father died, <f>ⓗ</f>God removed him from there into this land in which you are now living.
Acts 7-5 Yet he gave him no inheritance in it, not even a foot's length, but promised <f>ⓘ</f>to give it to him as a possession and to his offspring after him, <f>ⓙ</f>though he had no child.
Acts 7-6 And God spoke to this effect — that <f>ⓚ</f>his offspring would <f>ⓛ</f>be sojourners in a land belonging to others, who would enslave them and afflict them <f>ⓜ</f>four hundred years.
Acts 7-7 ‘But <f>ⓝ</f>I will judge the nation that they serve,’ said God, ‘and after that they shall come out <f>ⓞ</f>and worship me in this place.’
Acts 7-8 And <f>ⓟ</f>he gave him the covenant of circumcision. And <f>ⓠ</f>so Abraham became the father of Isaac, and <f>ⓡ</f>circumcised him on the eighth day, and <f>ⓢ</f>Isaac became the father of Jacob, and <f>ⓣ</f>Jacob of the twelve patriarchs.
Acts 7-9 <pb/>“And the patriarchs, <f>ⓤ</f>jealous of Joseph, <f>ⓥ</f>sold him into Egypt; but <f>ⓦ</f>God was with him
