Acts 7-32 <f>ⓒ</f> ‘I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham and of Isaac and of Jacob.’ And Moses trembled and did not dare to look.
Acts 7-33 Then the Lord said to him, <f>ⓓ</f>‘Take off the sandals from your feet, for the place where you are standing is holy ground.
Acts 7-34 <f>ⓔ</f> I have surely seen the affliction of my people who are in Egypt, and <f>ⓕ</f>have heard their groaning, and <f>ⓖ</f>I have come down to deliver them. <f>ⓗ</f>And now come, I will send you to Egypt.’
Acts 7-35 <pb/>“This Moses, whom they rejected, <f>ⓘ</f>saying, ‘Who made you a ruler and a judge?’ — this man God sent as both ruler and redeemer <f>ⓙ</f>by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush.
